.TH "batadv_reroute_unicast_packet" 9 "batadv_reroute_unicast_packet" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_reroute_unicast_packet \- update the unicast header for re-routing
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" batadv_reroute_unicast_packet
.BI "(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv "  ","
.BI "struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_unicast_packet *unicast_packet "  ","
.BI "u8 *dst_addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned short vid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bat_priv" 12
the bat priv with all the soft interface information
.IP "skb" 12
unicast packet to process
.IP "unicast_packet" 12
the unicast header to be updated
.IP "dst_addr" 12
the payload destination
.IP "vid" 12
VLAN identifier
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Search the translation table for dst_addr and update the unicast header with
the new corresponding information (originator address where the destination
client currently is and its known TTVN)
.SH "RETURN"
true if the packet header has been updated, false otherwise
